    <body class="- topic/body " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/embedding_diagrams_in_dita_topics_using_plantuml.dita" xtrc="body:1;14:11">
        <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/embedding_diagrams_in_dita_topics_using_plantuml.dita" xtrc="p:1;15:12"><xref href="https://plantuml.com/" format="html" scope="external" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/embedding_diagrams_in_dita_topics_using_plantuml.dita" xtrc="xref:1;15:78"><?ditaot usertext?>PlantUML</xref> is a
            neat library that takes textual descriptions of diagrams and produces visual diagrams
            from them. </p>
        <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/embedding_diagrams_in_dita_topics_using_plantuml.dita" xtrc="p:2;18:12">Suppose you have a DITA topic that embeds such a textual description of a diagram: <xref href="https://github.com/oxygenxml/dita-ot-diagrams-plugin/blob/master/com.oxygenxml.diagrams.svg/samples/testPlantUMLDiagram.dita" format="html" scope="external" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/embedding_diagrams_in_dita_topics_using_plantuml.dita" xtrc="xref:2;20:49"/>.</p>
        <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/embedding_diagrams_in_dita_topics_using_plantuml.dita" xtrc="p:3;21:12"><image id="image_lmd_jzh_ckb" href="../images/previewPlantUML.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/embedding_diagrams_in_dita_topics_using_plantuml.dita" xtrc="image:1;22:55" dita-ot:image-width="851" dita-ot:image-height="766" dita-ot:horizontal-dpi="120" dita-ot:vertical-dpi="120"/></p>
        <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/embedding_diagrams_in_dita_topics_using_plantuml.dita" xtrc="p:4;23:12">To provide support in Oxygen for using such diagrams in DITA topics, you need to install
            the following components:<ul id="ul_s2r_yyh_ckb" class="- topic/ul " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/embedding_diagrams_in_dita_topics_using_plantuml.dita" xtrc="ul:1;24:62">
                <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/embedding_diagrams_in_dita_topics_using_plantuml.dita" xtrc="li:1;25:21">An Oxygen plugin that presents PlantUML textual descriptions as images when
                    editing the content in the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/embedding_diagrams_in_dita_topics_using_plantuml.dita" xtrc="b:1;26:51">Author</b> visual editing mode: <xref href="https://github.com/oxygenxml/wsaccess-javascript-sample-plugins/tree/master/plantuml-images-support" format="html" scope="external" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/embedding_diagrams_in_dita_topics_using_plantuml.dita" xtrc="xref:3;28:57"/>. </li>
                <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/embedding_diagrams_in_dita_topics_using_plantuml.dita" xtrc="li:2;29:21">A DITA Open Toolkit publishing plugin that, once installed in the DITA Open
                    Toolkit, will convert the textual descriptions to diagrams for both the
                    HTML-based and PDF outputs: <xref href="https://github.com/oxygenxml/dita-ot-diagrams-plugin" format="html" scope="external" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/embedding_diagrams_in_dita_topics_using_plantuml.dita" xtrc="xref:4;33:43"/>.</li>
            </ul></p>
        <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/embedding_diagrams_in_dita_topics_using_plantuml.dita" xtrc="p:5;35:12">Once you have this setup, you can both visualize the diagrams when editing and publish
            them while having the diagram representations dynamically converted to SVG in the
            published output.</p>
